This the divx4linux backend, interface between the rte frontend
and the divx encoding library libdivxencore.so. Please note this
code is licensed under the GPL, however the libdivxencore.so and
its header file encore2.h are NON-FREE licensed.

The divx4linux backend will compile only if encore2.h is installed
on the system. It will run only if libdivxencore.so can be linked at
runtime. This directory contains no code by DivXNetworks, Inc. and
no such code is distributed with rte sources or binaries.

The GPL permits linking of GPLed programs with non-free software,
assuming the following exception applies to plug-ins: "If identifiable
sections of that work are not derived from the Program, and can be
reasonably considered independent and separate works in themselves,
then this License, and its terms, do not apply to those sections when
you distribute them as separate works."

No rights are granted to use or distribute divx4linux. Please see
the divx4linux license if you are allowed to use or distribute it.
